Data have shown that the average price of one medium-sized dozen of agric eggs decreased by -3.37 per cent to N456.81 in September 2019 from N461.89 in August 2019. The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) report on selected food prices for September showed that the average price of agric egg medium size (price of one) increased year-on-year by 0.32 per cent and month-on-month by 1.80 per cent to N41.30 in September 2019 from N40.57 in August 2019. Similarly, the average price of 1kg of tomato decreased by -30.69 per cent to N227.50 in September 2019 from N223.86 in August 2019. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Also, the average price of 1kg of rice (imported high quality sold loose) decreased year-on-year by -0.05 per cent and increased month-on-month by 4.07 per cent to N371.13 in September 2019 from N356.61 in August 2019. Likewise, the average price of 1kg of yam tuber decreased year-on-year by -32.13 per cent and increased month-on month by 0.10 per cent to N190.23 in September 2019 from N190.04 in August 2019. Meanwhile, two separate reports that monitored prices of kerosene and cooking gas used by households for cooking food showed that Nigerians also paid less in September compared to August. An NBS report showed that the average price per litre paid by consumers for National Household Kerosene decreased by -1.30 per cent to N318.46 in September 2019 from N322.64 in August 2019. States with the highest average price per litre of kerosene were Abia (N378.50), Enugu (N372.73) and Cross River (N359.85) while states with the lowest average price per litre of kerosene were Abuja (N245.83), Nasarawa (N265.92) and Borno (N276.96). For cooking gas, Daily Trust observed that the average price for the refilling of a 5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (cooking gas) decreased by -1.21 per cent in September 2019 from N2,000.34 in August 2019. States with the highest average price for the refilling of a 5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (cooking gas) were Bauchi (N2,481.88), Borno (N2,382.29) and Adamawa (N2,375.66) while states with the lowest average price for the refilling of a 5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (cooking gas) were Abuja (N1,680), Ebonyi (N1,700) and Osun (N1,711.46). Prices of egg, rice rose in June – NBS Prices of selected food stuff decreased in September – NBS Prices of egg, tomato, others drop in May – NBS